The top three finalists for the Race to the Top High School Commencement Challenge have been announced by the White House and the Department of Education. The finalists are Clark Montessori Jr. & Sr. High School in Cincinnati, OH, Kalamazoo Central High School in Kalamazoo, MI, and Denver School of Science and Technology in Denver, CO. President Obama will select a winner from these three schools to deliver their commencement address. The winner will be announced on May 4th. In recognition of the achievements of the other finalists, the Obama Administration will arrange for a Cabinet secretary or senior administration official to deliver the commencement address at each of the five schools that were not selected as the national winner. Over one thousand schools submitted applications for the challenge.